      <notesStmt>
        <note>Title from cover folio (f. 1r; reads: atha bhūtaśuddhiḥ prāraṁbhaḥ), f. 1v, and f. 10v (reads: iti bhūtaśuddhi samāptaḥ).</note>
        <note>The text is largely the same as that of UPenn Ms. Coll. 390, Item 1380. See also Item 597, Item 2858, etc.</note>
        <note>Scribe's name is Bhāskara Bhaṭṭa.</note>
        <note>Written 8-9 lines per leaf.</note>
        <note>Good condition. Paper somewhat brown. Orange powder rubbed in to highlight sectional headings and some words. Mistakes crossed through or blotched out with black.</note>
        <note>Begins, f. 1v: śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ atha bhūtaśuddhiprāraṁbhaḥ pṛthivyā merupṛṣṭha ṛṣiḥ kūrmo devatā sutalaṁ chaṁdaḥ āsane viniyogaḥ pṛthvī tvayā dhṛtā lokā devi tvaṁ viṣṇunā dhṛtā tvaṁ ca dhāraya māṁ devīṁ pavitraṁ kuru cāsanaṁ</note>
        <note>Text ends, f. 9r: paṁcāśadvarṇabhedair vihitavadanadoḥpādahṛtkukṣivakṣodeśāṁ bhāsvatkapardākalitaśaśikalām iṁdukuṁdāvadātāṁ akṣa[-]srakuṁbhaciṁtālikhitavarakarāṁ tryakṣarāṁ padmasaṁsthām achākalpāvatuchastanajaghanabharāṁ bhāratīṁ tāṁ namāmi catvāri vāk * ṛk</note>
        <note>Colophon, f. 9r: śakeṁ 1690 sarvadhārī nāma saṁvatsare jyeṣṭha śuddhapratīpadā cipulaṇakarabhāskarabhaṭṭena likhitaṁ</note>
      </notesStmt>
